==English==
===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|elevat|ing}}

#To [[raise]] (something) to a [[higher]] [[position]]; to [[lift]].
#To [[promote]] (somone) to a higher [[rank]].
#To [[ennoble]] or [[honour]]/[[honor]] (someone).
#To lift someone's [[spirit]]s; to [[elate]].
#To [[increase]] the [[intensity]] of something, especially that of [[sound]].

====Synonyms====
*(''raise''): [[lift]], [[raise]]
*(''promote''): [[promote]]
*(''ennoble''): [[ennoble]], [[honour]]/[[honor]]
*(''elate''): [[cheer up]], [[elate]]
*(''increase the intensity of''): [[increase]], [[raise]], [[turn up]], [[up]] {{informal}}

====Antonyms====
*(''raise''): [[drop]], [[lower]]
*(''promote''): [[demote]]
*(''ennoble''):
*(''elate''): [[depress]], [[sadden]]
*(''increase the intensity of''): [[decrease]], [[diminish]], [[lower]], [[reduce]], [[turn down]]

====Related terms====
*[[elevation]]
*[[elevator]]

